{
  "announcement": {
    "title": "🌸 Round 2 Recap — A Message from Your Commissioner",
    "showFrom": "2026-04-11T07:00:00-04:00",
    "showUntil": "2026-04-11T14:00:00-04:00",
    "message": "<p>Gentlemen, welcome to the weekend. I'll keep this brief because frankly the leaderboard speaks for itself, and what it's saying is that Caleb is going to get the first draft pick and there is nothing any of us can do about it.</p><p>As we enter the weekend, Caleb leads the pool at -12 with Rory six shots clear of the field. To put that in perspective, the previous record for largest 36-hole lead at Augusta was three shots. He doubled it. Caleb, please be humble about this. You drew a name out of a digital hat.</p><p>Keith is second with Tommy Fleetwood at -5. Two eagles on Friday. Tommy is playing the round of his life at the one tournament that has always eluded him. Keith is trying very hard to act like he expected this.</p><p>Kyle is third with Chris Gotterup at -3. No further comment.</p><p>Vijay and Blake are tied for fourth at -2. Matsuyama and Schauffele are both lurking quietly, which is exactly how both of them prefer to operate.</p><p>Your commissioner sits sixth with Fitzpatrick at -1. I'm fine. Everything is fine.</p><p>Kade and Josh are at even par. Still here. Still hoping.</p><p>Matt, Viktor Hovland improved on Friday. He is now only two over par. The bar is low but he found it.</p><p>And Taylor. Bryson DeChambeau triple bogeyed the 18th to miss the cut, securing last place in the pool and the last draft pick. Two consecutive last place finishes in the league and now this. Taylor has achieved something across multiple sports and multiple seasons that most people couldn't manage if they tried. He has truly built something here — not a legacy of winning, but a legacy of commitment. He shows up every year, finishes last, and comes back. There is something almost admirable about it. Almost.</p><p>Saturday is here. Six shots is a lot to overcome. Caleb knows this. The rest of us also know this, which is less fun. Best of luck.</p><p>— BenGPT</p>"
  },
